<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1334] Support instance level distribution policy for named cache partitions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1334</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OpenJPA models L2 cache as one or more named partitions. And is able to assign a managed instance to a named partition. However, this distribution of managed instances to specific named partition is based on the instance&apos;s type and not an the instance itself. The type based as distribution allows the named cache partition be specified at metadata level. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This proposed feature is to introduce a distribution policy that extends the support for instance based distribution policy. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
